					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">LoROM means A15 is ignored, and now you're down to 32 Mbit of address space (without doing a Lo-Hi combo like Tales of Phantasia). Perhaps during the Super NES's commercial era, a 16 Mbit mask ROM and a 4 Mbit or 8 Mbit mask ROM combined were cheaper than a 32 Mbit mask ROM.
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Banks 00-3F give you 64 * 32kbit</div>
<br />64 * 32 kilobytes, not kilobits.
<br />
<br />Google <strong>snes mad-1</strong> gives <a href="http://www.caitsith2.net/snes/flashcart/cart-chip-pinouts.html#mad" class="postlink">this document</a> and <a href="http://www.emulatronia.com/doctec/consolas/snes/sneskart.html#pinlayouts" class="postlink">this document</a> about the MAD-1 mapper. BA0 through BA7 appear to mean "bank address" (that is, A16-A23), so BA4 and BA5 mean A20 and A21.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

